# Stevens CPE Brand Guidelines

Reference: `Stevens-CPE-Brand-Guidelines-2025-10.pdf` in repo root.
Logo assets: `CPE-assets(logos)/CPE Canva/` (SVG format).

## Color Palette (Section 2.3)

| Name | Hex | Usage |
|------|-----|-------|
| Stevens Red | `#A32638` | Accents, table headers, KPI borders, primary brand color |
| Dark Gray | `#363D45` | Body text, secondary headings |
| Stevens Gray | `#7F7F7F` | Dividers, secondary text, muted elements |
| Light Gray | `#E4E5E6` | Alternating row backgrounds, subtle fills |
| Black | `#000000` | Primary text on light backgrounds |
| White | `#FFFFFF` | Primary text on dark backgrounds |

- Emphasize black and white for an "impactful and modern aesthetic"
- Stevens Red used sparingly — accents, not large fills
- NEVER use gradients, drop shadows, or embellishments on typography
- NEVER use opacity variants of Stevens Red

## Typography (Section 2.2)

- **Headlines**: Saira Regular (light weights only — Thin, Extra Light, Light)
- **Body text**: IBM Plex Sans (Regular weight for body, Bold for emphasis)
- **Fallback**: Arial / Arial Narrow when brand fonts unavailable
- All brand fonts are free on fonts.google.com
- Build hierarchy through dramatic size shifts and weight contrast, not color

## Logo Assets (Section 2.1)

Located in `CPE-assets(logos)/CPE Canva/`:
- **Primary** (stacked): `Stevens-CPE-logo-RGB_Primary-{variant}.svg`
- **Linear** (horizontal): `Stevens-CPE-logo-RGB_Linear-{variant}.svg` — min 2.5" / 250px wide
- **Abbreviated** (icon): `Stevens-CPE-logo-RGB_Abbreviated-{variant}.svg` — min 0.5" / 50px wide

Variants: `4C` (full color), `4C-BLK-bg` (on dark), `BLK` (single black), `WHT` (single white)

- On dark backgrounds use `*-4C-BLK-bg.svg` or `*-WHT.svg`
- On light backgrounds use `*-4C.svg` or `*-BLK.svg`
- Respect clear space around logos
- NEVER stretch, tilt, recolor, or add effects to logos

## Visual Gestures — Asterisms (Section 2.4)

- Thin lines (1px) at 0, 90, 25, -25 degree angles
- Only black, gray, or white — never Stevens Red
- One main asterism per composition, 3-5 rays from center
- At least one line should use a gradient fade for depth

## Existing CSS Variables (in iris-react)

The React app maps brand colors to CSS variables — use these:
- `--color-accent-primary` (Stevens Red)
- `--color-bg-base`, `--color-bg-surface`, `--color-bg-elevated`
- `--color-text-primary`, `--color-text-secondary`, `--color-text-muted`
- `--color-success`, `--color-warning`, `--color-danger`
- `--color-border-subtle`, `--color-border-default`
